com.cyc.session

Class ServerAddress

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyc.session.ServerAddress
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CycServer

    public class ServerAddress
extends Object
implements Serializable, Comparable
    ServerAddress describes a server's hostname and port. For example, "localhost:80" It is easily serializable via its toString() method to a string representation as host:port, and can be instantiated from strings matching that format via its static #fromString() method.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • isValidString

        public static boolean isValidString(String string)
        Tests whether a String could be deserialized into a valid ServerAddress. The string must match the format host:port, the host must be a valid hostname or IP address, and the port must be a valid port integer. Any string which is validated by this method should be a well-formed input for #fromString().
        Parameters:
        string - to evaluate
        Returns:
        whether it is a valid serialized ServerAddress address.

      • getResolvedHostName

        public String getResolvedHostName()
        Returns the resolved hostname of this address. If the hostname is a loopback address (e.g. 127.0.0.1 or localhost), it will be converted to a fully-qualified domain-name. Otherwise, it will return the specified hostname as per getHostName().

        Note that this value is not used by hashCode() or equals(Object). Equality is based off of the explicitly-specified values.

        Returns:
        String the resolved hostname.

      • resolveHostName

        public static String resolveHostName(String hostName)
        Resolves a hostname. If the hostname is a loopback address (e.g. 127.0.0.1 or localhost), it will be converted to the fully-qualified domain-name of the local address. If the hostname is not a loopback address, the original hostName parameter will be returned, unchanged.
        Parameters:
        hostName - the hostname to be resolved.
        Returns:
        String the resolved hostname.
